# CH HIGH SPEED BURST

Select the frame rate used when the drive dial is rotated to CH (continuous high speed). The display frame rate when the electronic shutter is used is 40 fps, or 60 fps in 1.29x crop mode.

| Options                  |                                                                 |
|--------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------|

Â³ 8.9 fps with electronic shutter.

# CL LOW SPEED BURST

Select the frame rate used when the drive dial is rotated to CL (continuous low speed).

| Options |        |
|---------|--------|
| 7.0fps* | 5.0fps |
| 3.0fps  |        |

* 6.7 fps with electronic shutter.

# HDR MODE

Each time the shutter button is pressed, the camera takes three shots, varying exposure each time, and combines them into a single picture. The resulting photograph preserves details in highlights and shadows (ðŸ“– 107).

# ADV. FILTER SETTING

Choose the filter used when the drive dial is rotated to ADV. (ðŸ“– 110).
